 chronicle his devotion to serving the people who became the United States both before and after the Revolution and to advancing his democratic vision of their future. Franklin’s humanity and genius have never seemed more real than in the pages of this appealing anthology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHommes d'ÉtatxArchivesxÉtats-Unis. 0aStatesmenxArchivesxUnited States. 0aStatesmenzUnited StatesvArchives. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / American / General.2bisacsh1 aMorgan, Edmund S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013501540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300135015423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300135015/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles